headline: Accenture (ACN) Undershoots Historic Growth—Value Narrative Holds as Margin Softness Challenges Bulls
summary: Accenture (ACN) reported earnings growth of 5.7% over the past year, trailing its five-year average of 7.4% per year. Net profit margin came in at 11%, slightly below last year’s 11.2%, while forward guidance calls for annual earnings growth of 8.75%. This is below the US market’s 15.4% earnings and 9.9% revenue growth expectations. Revenue is projected to rise 5.3% per year, also lagging the market.
